Pandas and Titanic Dataset Mock Exam

1 source

The sources consist of a comprehensive mock examination focused on Pandas and data analysis using the Titanic dataset, alongside its complete solutions and a detailed reference guide on Python help commands. The exam is structured into three sections: Conceptual Questions (defining Pandas terms like .loc[] vs. .iloc[]), Coding Questions (practical tasks involving data loading, cleaning, filtering, and aggregation), and Applied Data Analysis (exploratory visualization and interpretation of survival rates). The accompanying solutions provide both correct answers and code examples, reinforcing essential data manipulation techniques like handling missing data (using fillna and mode) and feature engineering. The final sections offer quick-reference cheatsheets and practical advice on leveraging the help(), ?, and dir() commands for efficient problem-solving during the test.
